     Aug. 20 (Bloomberg) - Three people were killed and more
than 111,000 were evacuated from their homes as Typhoon Kai-Tak
swept through southwest  China , the Xinhua News Agency reported
today, citing local civil affairs authorities.  The tropical storm, which hit Chinaâ€™s Guangxi Zhuang
autonomous region, also destroyed more than 2,800 hectares
(6,918 acres) of crops as of 4 p.m. today, the report said,
citing a statement from the civil affairs department.  Direct economic losses are estimated at 1.65 billion  yuan 
($259.4 million), the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
